53 TrajectoryGeneratorCIRC::TrajectoryGeneratorCIRC(const moveit::core::RobotModelConstPtr& robot_model,
54  const LimitsContainer& planner_limits)
55  : TrajectoryGenerator::TrajectoryGenerator(robot_model, planner_limits)
56 {
57  if (!planner_limits_.hasFullCartesianLimits())
58  {
59  throw TrajectoryGeneratorInvalidLimitsException(
60  "Cartesian limits are not fully set for CIRC trajectory generator.");
61  }
62 }

64 void TrajectoryGeneratorCIRC::cmdSpecificRequestValidation(const planning_interface::MotionPlanRequest& req) const
65 {
66  if (!(req.path_constraints.name == "interim" || req.path_constraints.name == "center"))
67  {
68  std::ostringstream os;
69  os << "No path constraint named \"interim\" or \"center\" found (found "
70  "unknown constraint: "
71  << "\"req.path_constraints.name\""
72  << " instead)";
73  throw UnknownPathConstraintName(os.str());
74  }
75 
76  if (req.path_constraints.position_constraints.size() != 1)
77  {
78  throw NoPositionConstraints("CIRC trajectory generator needs valid a position constraint");
79  }
80 
81  if (req.path_constraints.position_constraints.front().constraint_region.primitive_poses.size() != 1)
82  {
83  throw NoPrimitivePose("CIRC trajectory generator needs valid a primitive pose");
84  }
85 }

87 void TrajectoryGeneratorCIRC::extractMotionPlanInfo(const planning_scene::PlanningSceneConstPtr& scene,
88  const planning_interface::MotionPlanRequest& req,
89  TrajectoryGenerator::MotionPlanInfo& info) const
90 {
91  ROS_DEBUG("Extract necessary information from motion plan request.");
92 
93  info.group_name = req.group_name;
94  std::string frame_id{ robot_model_->getModelFrame() };
95 
96  // goal given in joint space
97  if (!req.goal_constraints.front().joint_constraints.empty())
98  {
99  // TODO: link name from goal constraint and path constraint
100  info.link_name = req.path_constraints.position_constraints.front().link_name;
101  if (!robot_model_->hasLinkModel(info.link_name))
102  {
103  throw UnknownLinkNameOfAuxiliaryPoint("Unknown link name of CIRC auxiliary point");
104  }
105 
106  if (req.goal_constraints.front().joint_constraints.size() !=
107  robot_model_->getJointModelGroup(req.group_name)->getActiveJointModelNames().size())
108  {
109  std::ostringstream os;
110  os << "Number of joint constraint = " << req.goal_constraints.front().joint_constraints.size()
111  << " not equal to active joints of group = "
112  << robot_model_->getJointModelGroup(req.group_name)->getActiveJointModelNames().size();
113  throw NumberOfConstraintsMismatch(os.str());
114  }
115 
116  // initializing all joints of the model
117  for (const auto& joint_name : robot_model_->getVariableNames())
118  {
119  info.goal_joint_position[joint_name] = 0;
120  }
121 
122  for (const auto& joint_item : req.goal_constraints.front().joint_constraints)
123  {
124  info.goal_joint_position[joint_item.joint_name] = joint_item.position;
125  }
126 
127  computeLinkFK(robot_model_, info.link_name, info.goal_joint_position, info.goal_pose);
128  }
129  // goal given in Cartesian space
130  else
131  {
132  info.link_name = req.goal_constraints.front().position_constraints.front().link_name;
133  if (req.goal_constraints.front().position_constraints.front().header.frame_id.empty() ||
134  req.goal_constraints.front().orientation_constraints.front().header.frame_id.empty())
135  {
136  ROS_WARN("Frame id is not set in position/orientation constraints of "
137  "goal. Use model frame as default");
138  frame_id = robot_model_->getModelFrame();
139  }
140  else
141  {
142  frame_id = req.goal_constraints.front().position_constraints.front().header.frame_id;
143  }
144  geometry_msgs::Pose goal_pose_msg;
145  goal_pose_msg.position =
146  req.goal_constraints.front().position_constraints.front().constraint_region.primitive_poses.front().position;
147  goal_pose_msg.orientation = req.goal_constraints.front().orientation_constraints.front().orientation;
148  normalizeQuaternion(goal_pose_msg.orientation);
149  tf2::fromMsg(goal_pose_msg, info.goal_pose);
150  }
151 
152  assert(req.start_state.joint_state.name.size() == req.start_state.joint_state.position.size());
153  for (const auto& joint_name : robot_model_->getJointModelGroup(req.group_name)->getActiveJointModelNames())
154  {
155  auto it{ std::find(req.start_state.joint_state.name.cbegin(), req.start_state.joint_state.name.cend(), joint_name) };
156  if (it == req.start_state.joint_state.name.cend())
157  {
158  std::ostringstream os;
159  os << "Could not find joint \"" << joint_name << "\" of group \"" << req.group_name
160  << "\" in start state of request";
161  throw CircJointMissingInStartState(os.str());
162  }
163  size_t index = it - req.start_state.joint_state.name.cbegin();
164  info.start_joint_position[joint_name] = req.start_state.joint_state.position[index];
165  }
166 
167  computeLinkFK(robot_model_, info.link_name, info.start_joint_position, info.start_pose);
168 
169  // check goal pose ik before Cartesian motion plan starts
170  std::map<std::string, double> ik_solution;
171  if (!computePoseIK(scene, info.group_name, info.link_name, info.goal_pose, frame_id, info.start_joint_position,
172  ik_solution))
173  {
174  // LCOV_EXCL_START
175  std::ostringstream os;
176  os << "Failed to compute inverse kinematics for link: " << info.link_name << " of goal pose";
177  throw CircInverseForGoalIncalculable(os.str());
178  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP // not able to trigger here since lots of checks before
179  // are in place
180  }
181 
182  Eigen::Vector3d circ_path_point;
183  tf2::fromMsg(req.path_constraints.position_constraints.front().constraint_region.primitive_poses.front().position,
184  circ_path_point);
185 
186  info.circ_path_point.first = req.path_constraints.name;
187  info.circ_path_point.second = circ_path_point;
188 }

190 void TrajectoryGeneratorCIRC::plan(const planning_scene::PlanningSceneConstPtr& scene,
191  const planning_interface::MotionPlanRequest& req, const MotionPlanInfo& plan_info,
192  const double& sampling_time, trajectory_msgs::JointTrajectory& joint_trajectory)
193 {
194  std::unique_ptr<KDL::Path> cart_path(setPathCIRC(plan_info));
195  std::unique_ptr<KDL::VelocityProfile> vel_profile(
196  cartesianTrapVelocityProfile(req.max_velocity_scaling_factor, req.max_acceleration_scaling_factor, cart_path));
197 
198  // combine path and velocity profile into Cartesian trajectory
199  // with the third parameter set to false, KDL::Trajectory_Segment does not
200  // take
201  // the ownship of Path and Velocity Profile
202  KDL::Trajectory_Segment cart_trajectory(cart_path.get(), vel_profile.get(), false);
203 
204  moveit_msgs::MoveItErrorCodes error_code;
205  // sample the Cartesian trajectory and compute joint trajectory using inverse
206  // kinematics
207  if (!generateJointTrajectory(scene, planner_limits_.getJointLimitContainer(), cart_trajectory, plan_info.group_name,
208  plan_info.link_name, plan_info.start_joint_position, sampling_time, joint_trajectory,
209  error_code))
210  {
211  throw CircTrajectoryConversionFailure("Failed to generate valid joint trajectory from the Cartesian path",
212  error_code.val);
213  }
214 }

216 std::unique_ptr<KDL::Path> TrajectoryGeneratorCIRC::setPathCIRC(const MotionPlanInfo& info) const
217 {
218  ROS_DEBUG("Set Cartesian path for CIRC command.");
219 
220  KDL::Frame start_pose, goal_pose;
221  tf2::fromMsg(tf2::toMsg(info.start_pose), start_pose);
222  tf2::fromMsg(tf2::toMsg(info.goal_pose), goal_pose);
223 
224  const auto& eigen_path_point = info.circ_path_point.second;
225  const KDL::Vector path_point{ eigen_path_point.x(), eigen_path_point.y(), eigen_path_point.z() };
226 
227  // pass the ratio of translational by rotational velocity as equivalent radius
228  // to get a trajectory with rotational speed, if no (or very little)
229  // translational distance
230  // The KDL::Path implementation chooses the motion with the longer duration
231  // (translation vs. rotation)
232  // and uses eqradius as scaling factor between the distances.
233  double eqradius = planner_limits_.getCartesianLimits().getMaxTranslationalVelocity() /
234  planner_limits_.getCartesianLimits().getMaxRotationalVelocity();
235 
236  try
237  {
238  if (info.circ_path_point.first == "center")
239  {
240  return PathCircleGenerator::circleFromCenter(start_pose, goal_pose, path_point, eqradius);
241  }
242  else // if (info.circ_path_point.first == "interim")
243  {
244  return PathCircleGenerator::circleFromInterim(start_pose, goal_pose, path_point, eqradius);
245  }
246  }
247  catch (KDL::Error_MotionPlanning_Circle_No_Plane& e)
248  {
249  std::ostringstream os;
250  os << "Failed to create path object for circle." << e.Description();
251  throw CircleNoPlane(os.str());
252  }
253  catch (KDL::Error_MotionPlanning_Circle_ToSmall& e)
254  {
255  std::ostringstream os;
256  os << "Failed to create path object for circle." << e.Description();
257  throw CircleToSmall(os.str());
258  }
259  catch (ErrorMotionPlanningCenterPointDifferentRadius& e)
260  {
261  std::ostringstream os;
262  os << "Failed to create path object for circle." << e.Description();
263  throw CenterPointDifferentRadius(os.str());
264  }
265 
266  return nullptr;
267 }
